Reason for gold plated electrical circuit contacts

1. Gold is the least likely medal to oxidize. Gold's electro-potential value is -1.1, meaning it should not oxidize at all, even in water.
2. It is an extremely conductive material, one of the best known behind graphene carbon, silver and copper.
3. Gold is very malleable, it is very easy to get a thin sheet of it.
